features: Complete Oral Care for 2 – AquaSonic Duo provides complete oral care in one simple countertop setup. Duo features 2 modern smart toothbrushes with the latest oral care technologies including 40,000 vibration per minute motors, true wireless charging, 3 unique modes including modes for whitening teeth and gum health, 30-day battery life, in sleek midnight black and optic white brush handles. Duo Series comes with 12 additional accessories including 10 DuPont brush heads and 2 travel cases.

Modern Technology For A Healthier Smile - Each Duo toothbrush bring your oral health routine into modern times with its built in enhanced features. Super fast wireless charging, 3 distinct brushing modes and a smart vibrating notification timer are some of the enhanced features built in to the sleek and ergonomic waterproof black and white satin handles.

Convenient Modern Home & Travel Set-Up – Duo is perfect for couples, kids or anyone in between. A simple dual wireless charging dock takes up a few inches of countertop space while adding a sleek modern element to your bathroom. Duo’s 30 day battery life means it’s also perfect for travel – simply put your duo in its included travel case and take it on the go while leaving the charger at home.

All The Extras; Already Included - Every DUO set comes with 10 brush heads engineered by world famous DuPont; a world leader in quality & materials science. Also included are 2 convenient color coded custom hard shell travel case made of BPA Free plastic with space for two brush heads. No need to buy expensive brush head refills or extra accessories. It’s already in the box.
What's Included - 1 Midnight Black Smart Toothbrush, 1 Optic White Smart Toothbrush, 1 Dual Wireless Charging Dock, 2 Travel Cases, 10 DuPont Brush Heads, Support & Warranty Manuals.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Three Years of Excellence: A Reliable Whitening Toothbrush
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this as a Christmas present for my wife and myself in November 2020. Fast forward to today, and it's still going strong after three years of regular use.The durability of this toothbrush is impressive. Only last week we noticed that the battery wasn't lasting as long as it used to, barely making it through a single use before needing a recharge. However, given the overall longevity and performance, I'm willing to explore options for replacing the battery. If that doesn't work out, I wouldn't hesitate to repurchase this model.In those three years, this has never let us down. In fact, it's been a cost-effective choice compared to cheaper brushes or manual ones. The initial price, which seemed like an investment at the time, more than paid off with its consistent performance and longevity.One standout feature is the convenient carrying case, making it easy to travel with. The toothbrush's battery life is exceptional, allowing for extended use even during extended trips. I've been on two-week journeys and never had to charge it more than once, even while brushing three times daily.What we truly love is the systematic approach it provides for teeth cleaning. With a built-in timer and a recommended pattern for cleaning, you're guided through each session, ensuring that every section of your mouth gets the attention it deserves. The first time I used this toothbrush, I was amazed at how fresh and clean my mouth felt. It was like a professional dental cleaning from the comfort of my own home.The Aquasonic Duo has been a reliable, long-lasting, and cost-effective addition to our daily oral care routine. It's designed for convenience, travel, and precision in cleaning, and it has truly revolutionized our approach to dental hygiene. If you're in search of a dependable electric toothbrush, look no further. This is a purchase that keeps on giving and leaves your mouth feeling brand new after every use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Stylish and efficient. Does a great job as well. Should have bought them earlier on.

Bought these for hubby & I, and I'm definitely glad I did. There's 3 settings and the 3rd is absolutely intense. If you have a sensitive mouth I wouldn't suggest that setting but it's amazing. They sit on the charging dock so they're always fully charged, nice size to keep beside the sink as well. There's a 2 min timer on them, every 30s it pauses to let you know. At the 2 min mark it auto shuts off.If you finish before the 2 mins you'll have to press the button up to 3 times to turn it off depending on which setting you chose to brush with. If you use the 3rd setting you just need to click once. They also come with great plastic durable cases and a very good number of replaceable heads.I definitely recommend these.
